gurmukhi: ਨਾਹਿਨ ਅਨੂਪ ਰੂਪ ਚਿਤਵੈ ਕਿੳੁ ਚਿੰਤਾਮਣਿ ਲੋਨੇ ਹੈ ਨ ਲੋੲਿਨ ਜੋ ਲਾਲਨ ਬਿਲੋਕੀਅੈ
transliteration: Naahin Anoop Roop Chitavai Kiu Chintaamani , Lonay Hai N Loin Jo Laalan Bilokeeai ?
translation: My looks are not attractive. Then how can I remember and conceive the beautiful? Lord the fulfiller of desires Lord? My eyes are not good looking; then how can I see the glimpse of that beloved Lord?

gurmukhi: ਰਸਨਾ ਰਸੀਲੀ ਨਾਹਿ ਬੇਨਤੀ ਬਖਾਨੳੁ ਕੈਸੇ ਸੁਰਤਿ ਨ ਸ੍ਵਨਨ ਬਚਨ ਮਧੋਕੀਅੈ
transliteration: Rasanaa Raseelee Naahi Baynatee Bakhaanau Kaisay , Surati N Sravanan Bachan Madhokeeai ?
translation: My tongue is not ambrosial. Then how can I make an effective request to my beloved? I do not have such power of hearing that I can enjoy the honey-like words of my beloved Lord?

gurmukhi: ਅੰਗ ਅੰਗਹੀਨ ਦੀਨ ਕੈਸੇ ਬਰ ਮਾਲ ਕਰੳੁ ਮਸਤਕ ਨਾਹਿ ਭਾਗ ਪ੍ਰਿਯ ਪਗ ਧੋਕੀਅੈ
transliteration: Ang Angaheen Deen Kaisay Bar Maal Karau , Masatak Naahi Bhaag Priy Pag Dhokeeai ?
translation: I am weak and imperfect in every part of my body. Then how can I make a superior rosary of remembrance of my Lord's name? I have no I can bank upon to wash the feet of my beloved.

gurmukhi: ਸੇਵਕ ਸ੍ਵਭਾਵ ਨਾਹਿ ਪਹੁਚ ਨ ਸਕੳੁ ਸੇਵ ਨਾਹਿਨ ਪ੍ਰਤੀਤ ਪ੍ਰਭ ਪ੍ਰਭਤਾ ਸਮੋਕੀਅੈ ॥੬੪੦॥
transliteration: Sayvak Svabhaav Naahi Pahouch N Sakau Sayva , Naahin Prateet Prabh Prabhataa Samokeeai ?640?
translation: I do not have the temperament of service in my heart; so I cannot reach for the service of my beloved. Nor do I have that devotion through which I can become one with the greatness of the dear Lord. (The greatness of the Lord may reside in me.)  (640)
